it to us to individuals or entities who work on our behalf or with us. These persons may use your PII to help fulfill your requests or communicate with you about different products and services that we offer. For instance, we may transfer PII and other information submitted by you to third parties who assist us in operating our business and/or the Website.\n<strong>Under what other circumstances may we release PII?</strong>\nWe may also release your PII (i) if we believe such release is necessary to comply with the law (e.g., a legal process or a statutory authorization), (ii) to apply or enforce our third party agreements, (iii) to protect our rights or property or to protect you from fraudulent, abusive, or unlawful use of the Website, or (iv) if we reasonably believe that a danger to any person requires disclosure of such PII.\n<strong>What other information does Operator collect?</strong>\nWe also may collect anonymous and aggregate information from you about your preferences in navigating the Website by using cookies, action tags and other methods. Cookies are small text files that identify your computer. We may use cookies to, among other things, monitor Website usage, customize Website features, identify your computer operating system and browser, and complete transactions. An action tag is a small, graphic image on a webpage that is designed to allow the website owner or a third party to monitor who is visiting a website by collecting the IP address of the computer to which the tag is sent, the URL of the webpage that the tag comes from and the time that such webpage was viewed. Action tags may be associated with cookie information. We may also use such anonymous and aggregate information for promotional purposes.\n<strong>Do I have the ability not to be identified by Operator?</strong>\nWe also may collect anonymous and aggregate information from you about your preferences in navigating the Website by using cookies, action tags and other methods. Cookies are small text files that identify your computer. We may use cookies to, among other things, monitor Website usage, customize Website features, identify your computer operating system and browser, and complete transactions. An action tag is a small, graphic image on a webpage that is designed to allow the website owner or a third party to monitor who is visiting a website by collecting the IP address of the computer to which the tag is sent, the URL of the webpage that the tag comes from and the time that such webpage was viewed. Action tags may be associated with cookie information. We may also use such anonymous and aggregate information for promotional purposes.\n<strong>How do we store information?</strong>\nOperator takes steps consistent with commercially reasonable industry standards to secure any PII collected from you from loss, misuse, unauthorized access and destruction while under our control. However, please note that despite our efforts to protect information provided to us, we cannot guarantee that such information will not be lost, disclosed or accessed by accidental circumstances or by the unauthorized acts of others.\n<strong>Does Operator provide links to other websites?</strong>\nOperator may provide links to other websites or resources. The collection and use of your PII and other information by such websites shall be subject to the policies and procedures of such websites and not the Privacy Policy.\n<strong>What are our policies regarding children?</strong>\nThe Website is a general use website and Operator does not knowingly collect PII from anyone under thirteen (13) years of age. If you are under thirteen (13) years of age, you are not authorized to submit any PII to us.\n<strong>Do we have a mechanism to address the removal of PII and complaints about the handling of information that we collect?</strong>\nIf you wish to remove PII that you have submitted to Operator, please send us an email requesting such removal to info@optionmetrics.com. If you have questions or concerns about any of our information collection or handling practices, please contact us at info@optionmetrics.com.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section]', 'Privacy Policy', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'privacy-policy', '', '', '2019-04-14 18:43:17', '2019-04-14 18:43:17', '', 0, 'http://localhost/omsite/?page_id=1140', 0, 'page', '', 0),
